# Build artifacts and VCS metadata — never needed in the image build context.
# Excluding target/ keeps the context small AND keeps cargo-chef's cook-layer
# cache stable (a bare `COPY . .` would otherwise invalidate it whenever target/
# changes). CI builds from a fresh checkout, so this is belt-and-braces there and
# load-bearing for local `docker build`.
target
.git

# Secret material — MUST never enter the build context. The Dockerfile does
# `COPY . .` (planner + builder) and then `COPY --from=builder .../configs ./configs`
# into the final runtime image, so an un-ignored `.env`/`configs/keys.json` would
# bake real provider keys and `rp_` gateway virtual keys into an image layer. These
# are already gitignored (so CI's clean checkout never had them), but a local
# `docker build` or the CE `docker compose up --build` quickstart — which tells you
# to write real keys into `configs/keys.json` first — would otherwise leak them.
# CE supplies keys.json at runtime via a read-only bind-mount, so excluding it here
# is a no-op for a working self-host.
.env
.env.*
configs/keys.json
configs/keys.json.bak
